The paper deals with massively parallel computation and graph algorithms, which are core topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The focus on sublinear memory and low-degree subgraphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the area of sparse graph algorithms (cs.DM). The use of randomized algorithms and the need for derandomization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the area of probabilistic algorithms (cs.CC). Finally, the application of the techniques to problems in network engineering (cs.NE) suggests that this may also be a relevant sub-category.
